{"actor":"charly vibes","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-05T19:52:52Z","event_type":"updated","id":155,"issue_id":"nayra-3ab","new_value":"{\"description\":\"The central reducer in src/core/store.js is growing too large. Recommendation: Use a combineReducers pattern to split the logic into focused modules: viewport, events, search, and interaction. Acceptance: Store logic is modularized into separate files in src/core/reducers/. CRITICAL: Follow TDD and Tidy First.\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"nayra-3ab\",\"title\":\"Split large store reducer into domain-specific modules\",\"description\":\"The central reducer in src/core/store.js is growing too large, handling everything from viewport and search to interaction state. Recommendation: Use a combineReducers pattern to split the logic into focused modules (viewport, search, etc.). CRITICAL: Follow TDD and Tidy First.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"charly.vibes@proton.me\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-05T22:47:28Z\",\"created_by\":\"charly vibes\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-05T22:47:28Z\"}"}
{"actor":"charly vibes","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-05T19:52:57Z","event_type":"updated","id":156,"issue_id":"nayra-e55","new_value":"{\"description\":\"In src/core/scale.js, zooming out can cause the numerator to become zero due to integer division. Recommendation: Add a minimum numerator value. Acceptance: Add a unit test verifying that a scale with SPP 1e15 does not result in a numerator \\u003c 1. CRITICAL: Follow TDD and Tidy First.\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"nayra-e55\",\"title\":\"Fix scale breakdown when zooming out too far\",\"description\":\"In src/core/scale.js, zooming out can cause the numerator to become zero due to integer division, leading to a broken scale and potential division by zero in pxToTime. Recommendation: Add a minimum numerator value or use a more robust representation. CRITICAL: Follow TDD and Tidy First.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"charly.vibes@proton.me\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-05T22:47:33Z\",\"created_by\":\"charly vibes\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-05T22:47:33Z\"}"}
{"actor":"charly vibes","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-05T19:54:39Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":157,"issue_id":"nayra-089","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"nayra-089\",\"title\":\"Support deep time in Wikidata transformer\",\"description\":\"The wikidata-transformer.js converts all dates to BCE notation, which causes errors in the time parser for geological/cosmological dates that exceed the JavaScript Date limit. Recommendation: Detect deep time precision and use Ga/Ma notation (e.g., -13.8 Ga). CRITICAL: Follow TDD and Tidy First.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"charly.vibes@proton.me\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-05T22:47:43Z\",\"created_by\":\"charly vibes\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-05T22:47:43Z\"}"}
